subproject.description:
Improved policy making and alightment of public administration reform with national priorities as well as strengthened management and capacities of key ministries through policy advice, exchange of experience and targeted technical assistance;

The goal of the project is to enhance government capacity in implmentation of public sector and economic reforms. The achievement of the above goal will be ensured by enhancing capacities of selected public institutions through assistance from the Capacity Building Fund. 

The project aims to complement the results of the initatives supported under the CBF Round 1 and 2. It will support the strategic proposals of the key national institutions aimed at building their capacities. The sub-projects of the priority nature will be supported through the fund. Implementation of the proposed sub-projects is expected to result in an enhancing technical and managerial capacities of selected public institutions in the most strategic directions.

